The specific emission constant for Iridium is incorrect. In Canada we use 480mR/hr not 520 or 590 like in the settings. I have emailed asking to have it fixed with no reply. It is a big difference in value and can alter our times quite significantly. Hopefully you can change it.
replyContent:
Can't remember receiving this email, otherwise I would have answered surely. When did you send it? Can you send that info again?
Beside that, the values in the app are "H/hr/Ci @ 1foot", your value is for  meter distance isn't it?
in that case, 5.2 is the value to use for you (5.2 R/hr/Ci @ 1foot eq. to 483 mR/hr/Ci @ 1 meter)
